            The
crisis began small, with the failure of a few <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">financial institutions</ENAMEX> that had
bet too heavily that the boom would continue, and the bankruptcy of a few
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">corporations</ENAMEX> that had taken on too much debt. These failures frightened
<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">investors</ENAMEX>, whose attempts to pull their money out led to more bank failures;
